Jeanette Chabalala, News24Reverend Canon Mpho Tutu and Professor Marceline van Furth. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Reverend Canon Mpho Tutu and Professor Marceline van Furth tied the knot on Wednesday.&nbsp;The couple reportedly married in a private ceremony held in Oegstgeest in the Netherlands. &nbsp;Tutu is currently the executive director of the Desmond and Leah Tutu Legacy Foundation, while Furth is a professor in Pediatric Infectious Diseases at the Vrije University in Amsterdam, and holds the Desmond Tutu Chair in Medicine at the university.&nbsp;It is the second marriage for both.&nbsp;The couple is set to celebrate their wedding in Cape Town in May.Reverend Canon Mpho Tutu and Professor Marceline van Furth. (Supplied)24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.